title: Wagner boss says his mercenaries handing over control of Bakhmut to Russian troops
description: The head of the Wagner Group says his forces have started pulling out of Bakhmut and are handing over control to the Russian military.

title: Madeleine McCann reservoir search ends
description: The latest search for Madeleine McCann has ended in Portugal as tents were taken down and heavy machinery was removed from the site.

title: Three killed in shooting and knife attack by masked man
description: Three people have been killed and one injured in a shooting and stabbing in Japan, with the suspect having barricaded himself inside a building, according to local media reports.

title: Mass brawl breaks out at airport baggage claim
description: Footage of a mass brawl at an airport which left one person injured has gone viral on social media.

title: Police photograph site in Portugal as new Madeleine McCann search enters third day
description: Police are photographing an excavation site near the banks of a remote reservoir in Portugal as the new search for Madeleine McCann enters a third day.

title: Killer whales deliberately hitting boats causing some to sink
description: Researchers believe killer whales are deliberately hitting boats, causing some to sink, following a string of incidents off the southwestern tip of Europe.

title: Iran says it has successfully launched 2,000km-range ballistic missile
description: Iran has successfully launched a 2,000km-range (1,243m) ballistic missile, according to the country's state media - two days after the chief of Israel's armed forces raised the prospect of "action" against Tehran over its nuclear programme.

title: US Capitol rioter who was pictured with his feet on Nancy Pelosi's desk is jailed
description: A Capitol Hill rioter who was photographed with his feet on Democrat Nancy Pelosi's desk has been sentenced to four-and-a-half years in prison.

title: Ship grounded in Egypt's Suez Canal - one of world's busiest shipping routes
description: A ship has become stuck in Egypt's Suez Canal, one of the world's busiest shipping routes.

title: Doing the Nutbush: One country's strange love affair with Tina Turner
description: Many Australians feel a special connection to Tina Turner, with one of her early songs having found a unique place in the country's culture.
